3ï¸âƒ£ RESPONSIVE ACTIONS

Political, ethical, perception-based; numbers are fuzzy

These donâ€™t always affect flood mechanics directly, but strongly influence outcomes.

Examples
R1. Evacuation Priority Decision

Choose priority:

Children & elderly

Urban professionals

Migrant workers

Rohingya refugee camps

Each affects:

Trust

Media

Long-term stability

R2. Rohingya Camp Handling

Options:

Full evacuation (high backlash risk)

Partial aid (security risk)

No evacuation (humanitarian cost)

Hidden future consequences.

R3. Media Strategy

Transparency â†’ trust + panic

Control â†’ stability â€“ credibility

R4. Political Visit Scheduling

Allows funding but freezes operations.

R5. Inter-State Water Dispute Response

Assam vs Arunachal coordination impacts upstream releases.

